# Normalize all text files to LF in the repository AND in the working tree on
# every platform.
#
# Without this, Windows checks out with core.autocrlf=true (the default on the
# GitHub windows-latest runner), converting LF -> CRLF on checkout. Prettier's
# `endOfLine` defaults to "lf", so `prettier --check src/` then rejects EVERY
# file on Windows while passing on Linux/macOS. That mismatch was invisible
# while the format gate carried `continue-on-error: true`; making the gate real
# exposed it.
#
# `eol=lf` forces LF in the working tree too, so the local checkout, the repo,
# and Prettier all agree on every OS.
* text=auto eol=lf

# Binary files must never be line-ending converted.
*.png binary
*.jpg binary
*.jpeg binary
*.gif binary
*.ico binary
*.woff binary
*.woff2 binary
